# UI Backend

- Keep controllers thin and focused on request handling, delegation, and response assembly.
- Do not place business logic in controllers.
- Prepare all template-facing data in DTOs or view models before rendering.
- Never expose entities directly to the UI layer.
- UI endpoints should be read-optimized and return display-ready data for the specific screen or fragment.
- Include prepared fields for sorting, filtering, status badges, error summaries, and log display when the UI needs them.

```java
public record JobRowView(
    String id,
    String name,
    String statusLabel,
    String statusBadgeClass,
    String startedAt,
    String detailsUrl
) {}
```
